      "remarks": "Erd\\H{o}s and R\\'{e}nyi proved by the probabilistic method that there exists a set $A$ such that\\[\\sum_{n\\leq x}f_r(n)^2 \\ll x\\]and\\[\\lvert A\\cap [1,x]\\rvert\\gg x^{1/r}\\]for all $x$. \n\nRuzsa \\cite{Ru90} proved that the answer is yes for $r=2$."
    },
